Durban - A 40-year-old was jailed for 20 years for raping a 14-year-old in January this year. Msize Mvelase was convicted and sentenced in the Pietermaritzburg Regional Court. According to police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane the victim had been on her way to the shop when she was approached by the accused. "The accused told her that he was looking for someone and asked her if she knew that person. He then grabbed and dragged her to the nearby bushes where he raped her. The victim immediately went home and reported the incident to her aunt." "As they were discussing the incident, the members of the community came with the suspect as someone from the community witnessed the girl being dragged into the bushes. With the assistance of the community members, he managed to apprehend the accused and handed him over to the police." A case of rape was opened at Taylors Halt police station and was assigned to Plessislaer Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit for investigation. Daily News  